repo.description: The most widely used Python to C compiler
repo.name: cython

commit.message: Update known builtins version to Py3.14b1.

Declare builtin exceptions as builtin types, referencing them with their C type pointer.
This is now possible because we allow subtypes for them in type checks.
Make regex a little more concrete.
Add missing "GeneratorExit" to list of known exceptions.
Extend "builtin_exceptions.py" test to cover type inference for the instantiation of all exception types.
Infer type of exception variable for "except XyzError as exc".

milestone.description: First feature release after the cleanup releases 3.0 and 3.1.

title: Infer the types of builtin exceptions
